    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "855339ac_eee68f26",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 284,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-02T15:43:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I find these names confusing. I was thinking decodeX, decodeWidth etc are \"the X, width, etc we ask the decoder to decode\".\n\nBut it looks more like:\n\ndecodeX/Y is the destination we write into\ndecodeWidth/Height are the dimensions (cropped) we ask for from the decoder, here, but down below, we further modify them and use the new values as the scaled output from the decoder. Lastly, we use decodeWidth to determine how many pixels to colorXform.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 284,
        "startChar": 36,
        "endLine": 284,
        "endChar": 47
      },
      "revId": "45d5789caa1a3b26fa62bfdb3b1ba49df8f3c9b4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "22fe40ee_f142b764",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 298,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-02T15:43:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think you need to cast decodeX to a float. Won\u0027t multiplying a float by an int result in a float?\n\nSame for the casts below.\n\n(On a somewhat related note, when you computed scaleX and scaleY, I think you only need to cast one operand to float.)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 298,
        "startChar": 39,
        "endLine": 298,
        "endChar": 44
      },
      "revId": "45d5789caa1a3b26fa62bfdb3b1ba49df8f3c9b4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1c1872f8_72e4d082",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 298,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-03T18:29:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "True, it\u0027s a style choice to be super explicit about the casts...  But I don\u0027t think it\u0027s very consistent with Skia, removing them.",
      "parentUuid": "22fe40ee_f142b764",
      "revId": "45d5789caa1a3b26fa62bfdb3b1ba49df8f3c9b4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5832ae32_7d8de86e",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 309,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-02T15:43:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In this case, don\u0027t you need to update decodeWidth to be the same? As I understand it, the scaled_width is going to be the number of pixels you actually wrote. So down below, when you colorXform with decodeWidth, I think you might write off the memory in the case of downscaling? (Note that it doesn\u0027t use decodeHeight, but it does use rowsDecoded, which in the case of success was set to dstInfo.height().)\n\nI think maybe using more/different variables would help make this clearer.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 309,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 309,
        "endChar": 58
      },
      "revId": "45d5789caa1a3b26fa62bfdb3b1ba49df8f3c9b4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "85305eb9_2891487c",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 309,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-03T18:29:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah you\u0027re right, should be fixed and a little clearer now.",
      "parentUuid": "5832ae32_7d8de86e",
      "revId": "45d5789caa1a3b26fa62bfdb3b1ba49df8f3c9b4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ca6abff9_4919d6d0",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 353,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-02T15:43:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think rowsDecodedPtr does *not* take scaling into account, but decodeY *does*. I don\u0027t think it makes sense to add the two together.\n\nI think you want decodeY added to a scaled version of rowsDecodedPtr (which I *think* starts from 0, even if frameIsSubset).\n\nAlthough I get confused about whether rowsDecodedPtr (for SkCodec) was supposed to mean rows of input versus rows of output... I *think* what you want to tell the client is the scaled version, so they can fill the remaining rows, if necessary. Likewise, down below you want to know the number of lines you decoded to the output, so you only xform them.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 353,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 353,
        "endChar": 51
      },
      "revId": "45d5789caa1a3b26fa62bfdb3b1ba49df8f3c9b4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9aba83a9_34a8e074",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 353,
      "author": {
        "id": 5185
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-03T18:29:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It looks to me like it does take scaling into account - we\u0027ve been using it that way for scaled decodes and it has worked fine.  libwebp says:\nint last_y; // coordinate of the line that was last output\n\nSo that seems to me indicate that it is in terms of dst rows.\n\nI think this is fine.  The incomplete images on the test bots should verify - I realize this failed last time but that was potentially caused by a different bug.",
      "parentUuid": "ca6abff9_4919d6d0",
      "revId": "45d5789caa1a3b26fa62bfdb3b1ba49df8f3c9b4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3f7306fb_3b227137",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWebpCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 353,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-03T19:43:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e It looks to me like it does take scaling into account - we\u0027ve been using it that way for scaled decodes and it has worked fine.  libwebp says:\n\u003e int last_y; // coordinate of the line that was last output\n\u003e \n\u003e So that seems to me indicate that it is in terms of dst rows.\n\u003e \n\u003e I think this is fine.  The incomplete images on the test bots should verify - I realize this failed last time but that was potentially caused by a different bug.\n\nLooking at the places last_y is used (https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/libwebp/dec/webpi_dec.h?type\u003dcs\u0026q\u003dlast_y+package:%5Echromium$\u0026l\u003d39), it does look like it\u0027s the last y in the output.\n\nAnd I agree, the test should catch us. We would assume more lines were initialized if this is *not* the scaled version, so we\u0027d be leaving some lines uninitialized.",
      "parentUuid": "9aba83a9_34a8e074",
      "revId": "45d5789caa1a3b26fa62bfdb3b1ba49df8f3c9b4",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    }
  ]
